''~SideEditor'' is a plugin that floats a tiddlers editor by the story river side.

The purpose is a ''"live" view of the effects from your editing'' and to be able to scroll and reference stuff from other tiddlers while you edit. It is intended for full size screens.

''Demo'' there  ‚ü∂<br>
For this demo, the editor is intentionally extended to cover much of the //sidebar//. Access the sidebar by hovering above the ~SideEditor, or by toggling or re-sizing the ~SideEditor (see below). Should your testing mess up these instructions, just reload this page.

''Usage''

*''Toggle'' the ~SideEditor via the tiddler tool button <span class="mybutton">{{$:/core/images/chevron-right}}</span>
*''Move'' it via the two gray handles.
*''Re-size'' width via the lower right corner. Height is automatic from typing.
*''Flip'' between //Sidebar// and //~SideEditor// by hovering. Exact //flip zones// might take some familiarization but here's a {{PeekToggler}} to clue about some critical areas. (Peek feature not included in the plugin).

''Issues'' and intended eventual dev, see [[here|Issues]].

''Installation'' - grab, drag and drop the link $:/plugins/TWaddle/SideEditor into your TW.

